Entry.JapaneseText: なんか思ってたのと 全然違った……
Entry.EnglishText: They're nothing like I imagined them to be...

Entry.JapaneseText: 英雄っていうのとは、 違う感じがするよね
Entry.EnglishText: They are pretty far from the textbook definition of a "hero", aren't they?

Entry.JapaneseText: なんか、 がっかりなんだよな
そう？ わたしは親近感湧いたけど
Entry.EnglishText: Really, now? I can see a lot in them outside a simple title.

Entry.JapaneseText: ゴメンなさい…… 代わりなんて言ってて 全然役に立てなくて
Entry.EnglishText: I'm sorry... I didn't really make a good replacement for you, Miss <MIN>.

Entry.JapaneseText: いいえ……皆さん、 喜んでくださっていましたよ
Entry.EnglishText: On the contrary... I'm very pleased with your efforts.

Entry.JapaneseText: あなたは とても聞き上手だって
Entry.EnglishText: I believe you're a very good listener.

Entry.JapaneseText: それにカワイイって 評判でした
Entry.EnglishText: I heard you managed to build some reputation even in such small time!

Entry.JapaneseText: オレ…… あんまうまく<CLE>さんの 代わり、できなかった
Entry.EnglishText: I...don't think I really did much to help you.

Entry.JapaneseText: <CLE>さんの 役に立ちたかったのに
Entry.EnglishText: I wanted to be of use but...

Entry.JapaneseText: 十分だよ。おかげで 僕たちもゆっくり 会う時間ができたし
Entry.EnglishText: You were good enough! Thanks to you we managed to relieve our work to finally strike a conversation.

Entry.JapaneseText: さて、と…… 僕はこれで行くよ
Entry.EnglishText: Well, then...I think I'll be leaving now for my mission.

Entry.JapaneseText: 私も<CLE>さんと 一緒に行きます
Entry.EnglishText: I want to go with you, <CLE>. I want to help you.

Entry.JapaneseText: 村の人たちに行ってきなさいと 言われました
Entry.EnglishText: I've talked with the people from the village.

Entry.JapaneseText: ケガをする方もいるでしょう。 法術師の力は 必要じゃありませんか？
Entry.EnglishText: I believe there will be plenty of injured citizens. Wouldn't the Divine Power be useful to relieve some of that stress?

Entry.JapaneseText: いいや……助かるよ。 ありがとう
Entry.EnglishText: Yes, you're right... Thanks for your support.
No...I'm not doing this just for my duty. I want to do it to stay true to my feelings.

Entry.JapaneseText: <CLE>さんのそばで 戦いたいから
Entry.EnglishText: I want to fight along with you, <CLE>.

Entry.JapaneseText: <MEL>はちゃんと <MIN>さんの代わりできたのに、 オレ、ダメだったから……
Entry.EnglishText: <MEL> was able to help <MIN>. But I haven't helped at all...

Entry.JapaneseText: オレ、ちゃんと、 <CLE>さんの力になりたい！
Entry.EnglishText: I want to become Mister <CLE>' strength!

Entry.JapaneseText: オレの力でできること、 やりたいんだ！
Entry.EnglishText: I know I can help you if you give me a chance!

Entry.JapaneseText: わかってるの！？ ぼくたちの目的は……
Entry.EnglishText: Do you understand what that means? This is far from what we came here for...

Entry.JapaneseText: 虹輪はノルンの力が 抑えてくれてんだろ？
Entry.EnglishText: Norn's power can hold the Prism Ring for a little while, right?
It's just for a little while...

Entry.JapaneseText: 協力はありがたいし、 前に戦って 君の実力はわかってる
Entry.EnglishText: Thank you for lending your strength to me. I understand your resolve.

Entry.JapaneseText: でも、敵は誰も 手加減してくれないし、 情けも容赦もない
Entry.EnglishText: However, it will be a ruthless battle. The enemy will have no mercy.

Entry.JapaneseText: 足手まといになんなら、 捨ててってくれていい
Entry.EnglishText: If I become a burden just drop me from the mission.

Entry.JapaneseText: ……わかった。 その覚悟があるなら
わたしも行きます。 <DIO>ひとりじゃ 心配すぎるから
Entry.EnglishText: I'm going too. I'll only grow worried if <DIO> goes all on his own.

Entry.JapaneseText: 聖なる力がきっと あなたたちの今後の戦いを 支えてくれるはずです
Entry.EnglishText: With this clothing you should be able to tap into divine powers even further. I trust it will prove useful in your journeys.

Entry.JapaneseText: ありがとうございます
それじゃあ、 準備が済んだら 出発するとしよう
Entry.EnglishText: In any case, prepare yourselves. We will scramble whenever you're ready.
